<p class="">In addition, under present circumstances and under the present set-up, there is no real possibility of the consumer getting a say. Indeed, I have a pamphlet written by the Fabian <span id="1183" class="column-number" data-column-number="1183"></span> Society, who have come round to the view that it is essential that some new form of inquiry, preferably something like a Select Committee, should be set up with power to investigate these matters. Anyone who has been a Member, or who has read the accounts, of the Public Accounts Committee, knows that—</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
